    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the White House on September 26,
                        1940</hi>
                    <note n="20" type="source" xml:id="d144fn20">Reprinted from Department of State,
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 28, 1940 (vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, No. 66), p. 250.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1940-09-26">September 26, 1940</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The President has approved the early establishment of additional controls of the
                    exportation of iron and steel scrap with a view to conserving the available
                    supply to meet the rapidly expanding requirements of the defense program in this
                    country.</p>
                <p>Effective October 15, 1940 all outstanding balances of licenses which have been
                    granted pursuant to the existing regulations of July 26, <pb facs="0289" n="223"
                        xml:id="pg_223"/> 1940 for the exportation of No. 1 heavy melting steel
                    scrap will be revoked. On October 16, 1940 the exportation of all grades of iron
                    and steel scrap will be placed under the licensing system.</p>
                <p>Under the new regulations which will be made effective on October 16, 1940,
                    licenses will be issued to permit shipments to the countries of the Western
                    Hemisphere and Great Britain only.</p>
            </div>
